    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix lower layer callback execution in EMM-DEREGISTERED state\n\n### Summary\nThe EMM state machine in the UE was not properly executing registered lower layer callbacks when in the EMM-DEREGISTERED state. When `lowerlayer_success()` or `lowerlayer_failure()` were called while the UE was in this state, the expected callback functions registered via `emm_proc_lowerlayer_initialize()` were never invoked, causing procedures to hang or fail silently.\n\nThis issue was particularly noticeable during attach procedures where the UE would send an Attach Request but never receive confirmation that it was successfully delivered to the network, even though the lower layers reported success.\n\nThe root cause was in `EmmDeregistered()` state handler which simply returned `RETURNok` when processing `_EMMREG_LOWERLAYER_SUCCESS` and `_EMMREG_LOWERLAYER_FAILURE` primitives, instead of calling the appropriate `emm_proc_lowerlayer_success()` and `emm_proc_lowerlayer_failure()` functions like other EMM states do.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/EMM/SAP/EmmDeregistered.c`: Modified the handler for `_EMMREG_LOWERLAYER_SUCCESS` to call `emm_proc_lowerlayer_success(user->lowerlayer_data)` instead of returning `RETURNok` directly\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/EMM/SAP/EmmDeregistered.c`: Modified the handler for `_EMMREG_LOWERLAYER_FAILURE` to call `emm_proc_lowerlayer_failure(user->lowerlayer_data, false)` instead of returning `RETURNok` directly\n\n"
}